- "gems in each brand's crown" refers to the top 3 clothing items with the highest average ratings within each brand;
- "crown" is a metaphor for the brand;
- "gems" are metaphors for clothing items.

- 'Customer level' is determined by the average order value and the total number of orders;
- 'Premium' customers have an average order value greater than 50 and more than 5 orders;
- 'Gold' customers have an average order value greater than 20 and more than 2 orders;
- 'Silver' customers have an average order value greater than 10 and more than 1 order;
- 'Bronze' customers do not meet the criteria for 'Premium', 'Gold', or 'Silver'.

- 'Unique voices in the crowd' refers to distinct customer names;
- 'Shared their thoughts' refers to leaving reviews;
- 'Garments crafted by the weavers of the brand manager's loom' refers to clothing items produced by brands managed by users with the role of 'brand manager'.

- 'Top recommended' refers to the highest confidence score in the recommendations;
- 'Customers who have spent more than $100' refers to the total amount spent by the customer on clothing items;
- 'Brands that produce the most items' refers to the total number of items produced by each brand.

- 'top-rated' refers to items with the highest average ratings;
- 'most popular' refers to items with the highest total quantity sold;
- 'priciest brand' refers to the brand with the highest average price.

- "shone brightly" refers to brands with an average rating greater than 4;
- "light of customer satisfaction" represents the average rating of the brand;
- "wealth" represents the total revenue generated by the brand;
- "in descending order" means the results are sorted from the highest total revenue to the lowest.

- "Performance metrics" include average ratings and the difference between the brand's average rating and the overall average rating;
- "Preferred sizes" are determined based on each customer's past purchases;
- "Total revenue" is calculated by summing the product of quantity and price for each brand and size chart combination.

- 'Body type' refers to physical characteristics such as slim, athletic, etc.;
- 'Preferred size' is the size that customers typically choose for their clothing;
- 'Average order value' is the mean total cost of orders for a specific body type.

- 'preferred brand' refers to the brand a customer prefers based on their purchase history;
- 'preferred size' refers to the size a customer prefers based on their purchase history;
- 'loyal customers' refers to customers who have made multiple purchases.

- 'Nike' is a well-known brand in the clothing and footwear industry;
- 'Top-rated' refers to items with the highest ratings given by customers;
- 'Preference' is based on the customer's purchase history and ratings.

- 'garments' refers to clothing items;
- 'stars' refers to highly popular items;
- 'closets' refers to the collection of items a customer has purchased;
- 'tastes of others' refers to the preferences and ratings of other customers.

- "loyal customers" refers to those who have made multiple purchases;
- "cast their nets widely" refers to purchasing from a variety of brands;
- "favoring specific brands" indicates the preferred brands identified in the query;
- "wardrobe essentials" refers to the different types of clothing items (e.g., tops, bottoms, dresses);
- "treasures (total spend)" represents the total amount of money spent by the customer on items from their preferred brand;
- "average price of those garments" is the average price of items for each type of clothing.

- "preferred size" refers to the size that the customer finds most comfortable and suitable;
- "best-rated" refers to the highest average rating from customer reviews;
- "fits perfectly" means the measurements (chest, length, shoulder width, and sleeve length) of the item fall within the range of the customer's preferred size measurements.
